    contentEn: "Power outages can occur due to equipment failure, extreme weather, maintenance work, or overload during peak demand. If you experience a power outage, first check if it affects only your property (check your circuit breaker) or is a wider area outage. For area-wide outages, call the electricity emergency line 997 immediately. MOEI monitors the electrical grid 24/7 and typically dispatches crews within 30 minutes for unplanned outages.\n\nPlanned maintenance outages are announced at least 48 hours in advance via SMS, email, and the MOEI website. Customers registered with UAE PASS receive automatic notifications for planned outages in their area. Planned outages are typically scheduled during off-peak hours (midnight to 6 AM) to minimize disruption. If a planned outage will exceed 8 hours, MOEI provides temporary alternative power arrangements for affected residential customers.\n\nDuring outage restoration, MOEI prioritizes critical facilities (hospitals, water treatment plants, traffic systems), then residential areas, and finally commercial zones. Restoration time depends on the cause and extent of the outage. Customers can track outage status and estimated restoration times on the MOEI website or by calling 8005555. After restoration, customers should report any equipment damage that may have resulted from the outage for compensation assessment.",
